reviews.title: Would've got 5 starts
reviews.body: So the t-shirt itself is really nice, and I would definitely recommend getting one, it was done very nicely. However, customer services were pants. I had accidentally ordered the wrong size t-shirt, which is entirely my fault and I felt completely stupid for doing that, so when it arrived and I realised my mistake I contacted customer services and I offered to return the tshirt and pay for the return postage and for postage on a new correct sized tshirt, however customer services were having none of it. The problem was that it was a Christmas present for my husband and having a size small tshirt that was never going to fit him made the tshirt unusable and a complete waste. Yes it was totally my fault but having pleaded my case with the company they would not send a new one (despite offering to cover postage costs) so it left a bitter taste. I appreciate that they cant do that everytime someone makes a mistake on an order, but it was Christmas, the shirt  cheap, and it all left me feeling disappointed. I wasnt going to leave a review but you kept emailing me to leave one, so now I have.
